  <refnamediv>
    <refname>doetbx_ff2n</refname>
    <refpurpose>A function to compute a two-level full factorial design. </refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>
  <refsynopsisdiv>
    <title>Calling Sequence</title>
    <synopsis>B = doetbx_ff2n(n)</synopsis>
  </refsynopsisdiv>
  <refsection>
    <title>Arguments</title>
    <variablelist>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>n</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The number of input factors of the experiment.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
      <varlistentry>
        <term>B</term>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            The two-level full factorial design.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </varlistentry>
    </variablelist>
  </refsection>
  <refsection>
    <title>Description</title>
    <para>
          Finds all combinations of the n factors, with each having two levels 0 and 1.
    </para>
    <para>With a latex expression
          <latex>
            \begin{eqnarray}
    f(x,a,r) = \frac{1}{r^{-a}\Gamma(a)} \int_0^x t^{a-1} \exp\left(-rt\right) dt
    \end{eqnarray}
    </latex>
    </para>
  </refsection>
